			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			Greetings from the United Nations. This council is a democratic insitution but I will be leader for life. The UN first came to life 3 sets ago. Where it prospered rising as high as rank 7, but a civil war broke out taking most active members. After a while war came to the UN and I died after 2 days of fighting. I dispanded the council and was recruited into the great SS-Falcon. After serving under intellect I have learned new things and decided to retry the council and here we are now. The rules are simple and easy to follow and any act of treason will be dealt with harshly. <br />
<br />
RULES:<br />
1. DO not attack or harrass a member's or ally's physical or mental well-being.<br />
2. Follow any and all Archspace rules.<br />
3. Do not slander a member or ally.<br />
4. Vote within 24 hours of issues arrival or your vote will be forfeited.<br />
5. No council hopping.<br />
<br />
Every member will have one of six ranks.<br />
<br />
RANKS:<br />
1. Speaker<br />
2. Secretary of Defence<br />
3. Secretary of Foreign Affairs<br />
4. Secretary if Civil Matters<br />
5. Secretary of Economics<br />
6. Councilmen<br />
<br />
More information will be posted on the council forum.<br />
<br />
Every member will also have a status. A status is a title showing your standing, respect wise, with the council. More information will be posted on the council forum.<br />
<br />
STATUSES:<br />
-5. Expelled Member<br />
-4. Greatly Dishonored Member<br />
-3. Dishonored Member<br />
-2. Criminal<br />
-1. Petty Offender<br />
0. Newb Member<br />
+1. Experienced Member<br />
+2. Trusted Member<br />
+3. Noblemen/Noblewomen<br />
+4. Lord of the Council<br />
+5. Master of the Council<br />
<br />
Leave a reply if interested or just apply. In the application state your contacts(messengers, etc) and experience.<br />
<br />
Archmaster Garran						<P align=right> </P>
